"I used a greedy approach where I track the farthest index reachable while iterating through the array.
If at any point the current index exceeds the reachable range, I return false since we can't proceed further.
Otherwise, I keep updating the maximum reachable index.
If I complete the traversal, it means the last index is reachable, so I return true.
This solution runs in O(n) time and O(1) space."

class Solution {
    public boolean canJump(int[] nums) {
        int isReach = 0;
        for(int i = 0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(i > isReach){
                return false;
            }
            isReach = Math.max(isReach , i + nums[i]);
        }
        return true;
    }
}
